00:19:12,670 --> 00:19:17,110
I've thought something was going on ever since
 the kimchi container incident.

262
00:19:17,110 --> 00:19:20,230
But it ended up being like this?

263
00:19:22,460 --> 00:19:24,860
I'll ask you as one man to another.

264
00:19:24,860 --> 00:19:27,350
Do you like my sister?

265
00:19:27,350 --> 00:19:28,350
What's your name?

266
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:29,710
Cheon Yoon Jae.

267
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:33,000
That is not important right now.

268
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,720
I asked you if you like my noona?

269
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,200
Are you laughing?

270
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:40,670
You sit a person in front of you, and then you laugh?

271
00:19:40,670 --> 00:19:42,900
It wasn't me who sat you down there.

272
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:45,740
You came in on your own and sat down yourself.

273
00:19:46,480 --> 00:19:48,730
That's true, of course.

274
00:19:48,730 --> 00:19:52,670
Man to man, male to male, I've come to ask you.

275
00:19:53,540 --> 00:19:57,290
I'm asking you if you like my sister?

276
00:19:58,310 --> 00:19:59,930
Would you like some chocolate milk?

277
00:19:59,930 --> 00:20:01,770
Do you have some?

278
00:20:09,590 --> 00:20:13,930
Lots of guys have chased my sister 
from the time she was a student,

279
00:20:13,930 --> 00:20:16,100
so I was busy finishing them off.

280
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:18,950
It's her first time liking a guy.

281
00:20:18,950 --> 00:20:22,880
I really don't know why, but...

282
00:20:24,130 --> 00:20:28,990

283
00:20:35,870 --> 00:20:37,690
 This  is a refraction telescope, isn't it?!

284
00:20:37,690 --> 00:20:39,550
Yeah.

285
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:44,240
How far can you see with this?

286
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:46,640
You can see to Jupiter and Saturn.

287
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:48,920
Awesome!

288
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,430
And this...

289
00:20:59,290 --> 00:21:03,760
Limiting magnitude of 13.28 and light gathering power of 816.32.

290
00:21:03,760 --> 00:21:08,700
It's a reflecting telescope that can view 
the Andromeda Galaxy, nebulae, and even star clusters.

291
00:21:08,700 --> 00:21:11,450
Are these all yours, Hyung?

292
00:21:11,450 --> 00:21:12,990
Yeah.

293
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,730
Can I ask for just one favor?

294
00:21:16,730 --> 00:21:17,490
Go ahead.

295
00:21:17,490 --> 00:21:21,650
Can I take a selfie next to this 'guy'?

296
00:21:21,650 --> 00:21:23,410
Take some.

297
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:38,260
If you like stars, do you want these pictures?

298
00:21:40,630 --> 00:21:42,470
This...

299
00:21:42,470 --> 00:21:44,830
That's right, Atacama Desert.

300
00:21:44,830 --> 00:21:49,770
Atacama Desert in Chile. When I earn money, 
my wish is to go there.

301
00:21:49,770 --> 00:21:52,990
That is my most favorite place on earth.

302
00:21:52,990 --> 00:21:56,940
Maximum sunlight, dry, and the sky is so clear

303
00:21:56,940 --> 00:22:01,260
that at night it makes one feel as if the stars are falling.

304
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:08,180
Like I said earlier, in March of 2014,

305
00:22:08,180 --> 00:22:11,830
don't believe the story that the asteroid "2003 QQ47"
will collide with Earth

306
00:22:11,830 --> 00:22:14,130
and bring about Earth's destruction.

307
00:22:14,130 --> 00:22:17,650
And don't say that you're going to give up studying because of that, either.

308
00:22:17,650 --> 00:22:20,710
I heard it from NASA, so I thought it was for real.

309
00:22:20,710 --> 00:22:22,440
It isn't true?

310
00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:24,180
At the time of discovery, NASA forecast the odds

311
00:22:24,180 --> 00:22:27,030
of collision at 1 in 250,000, but

312
00:22:27,030 --> 00:22:31,130
they announced the probability of collision was nil, immediately after.

313
00:22:31,130 --> 00:22:32,800
I see.

314
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:36,760
I'll trust you and make sure I won't quit studying
just because the asteroids are colliding.

315
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:41,280
I'm really stoked to have met someone who speaks
the same language as me on a rare chance.

316
00:22:42,620 --> 00:22:46,540
My sister... lacks in many ways,

317
00:22:46,540 --> 00:22:52,080
and comes up really short against you, 
but please treat her well.

318
00:22:54,310 --> 00:22:57,520
I would like to say something with that in mind.

319
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:02,330
May I visit again?

320
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,900
Yes?

321
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:19,660
My Song Yi is here.

322
00:23:23,040 --> 00:23:25,020
Come here.

323
00:23:42,660 --> 00:23:44,720
What's the matter?

324
00:23:44,720 --> 00:23:48,420
My heart is racing and I might faint again.

325
00:23:48,420 --> 00:23:50,410
Dummy.

326
00:23:50,410 --> 00:23:53,790
What if you had died?

327
00:23:53,790 --> 00:23:55,810
Why did you do that?

328
00:23:55,810 --> 00:23:59,170
How could I die and leave you?

329
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:10,610
If something had happened to you, 
I wouldn't have been able to live with myself.

330
00:24:10,610 --> 00:24:15,170
How could I live? 
Why would you... for me?

331
00:24:16,740 --> 00:24:19,950
I've never done anything for you.

332
00:24:19,950 --> 00:24:24,880
Hey, Cheon Song Yi, you allowed me to love you.

333
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:32,090
Let's see. You're not scarred or hurt anywhere?

334
00:24:34,690 --> 00:24:36,490
Hui Kyeong,

335
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:40,300
I'm sorry.

336
00:24:41,350 --> 00:24:42,380
Don't cry.

337
00:24:42,380 --> 00:24:48,870
Even if you do this for me, 
there's still nothing that I can do for you.

338
00:24:50,630 --> 00:24:54,070
I think I'm making you unhappy.

339
00:24:54,070 --> 00:24:55,550
I...

340
00:24:58,170 --> 00:25:00,620
like Do Min Joon.

341
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:04,920
I can't help it.

342
00:25:07,320 --> 00:25:11,550
I know. I can't help myself either, though.

343
00:25:13,010 --> 00:25:17,600
Hey, stop that.
 I'm really going to be miserable then.

344
00:25:20,960 --> 00:25:25,020
I don't know if I can live without my friend, Lee Hui Kyeong,

345
00:25:25,020 --> 00:25:27,770
but I don't think this is right.

346
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:31,250
- Let's....
- Chance!

347
00:25:35,660 --> 00:25:37,590
 Let's go.

348
00:25:40,340 --> 00:25:42,250
 Hui Kyeong, are you alright?

349
00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:44,230
 Chance!

350
00:25:44,230 --> 00:25:46,750
 Hey, what is this "chance" in a situation like this?

351
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:49,170
 Why, you said you were thankful!

352
00:25:49,170 --> 00:25:51,440
 Let me get one "chance" to use later.

353
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:53,170
 Who told you to get involved?

354
00:25:53,170 --> 00:25:57,160
 Whether boys bother me or not, 
why are you getting involved and ending up like this?

355
00:25:57,160 --> 00:25:58,680
 This can't be.

356
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:01,920
 Anyone who bothers you will be dead by me!

357
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:04,150
 It continues the same from now on.

358
00:26:04,840 --> 00:26:06,680
 Seriously.

359
00:26:08,910 --> 00:26:10,900
 Are you alright?

360
00:26:12,950 --> 00:26:17,670
 If you're sorry, I told you to just let me have one "chance" in return.

361
00:26:19,610 --> 00:26:21,330
 What "chance?"

362
00:26:22,170 --> 00:26:27,260
 Later, if I ask you for just one wish, 
please do it for me.

363
00:26:29,260 --> 00:26:30,230
 Okay.

364
00:26:30,230 --> 00:26:32,200
 Really?

365
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:37,200
 Sign.

366
00:26:42,670 --> 00:26:44,950
 Sealed.

367
00:26:52,470 --> 00:26:54,250
Do you remember?

368
00:26:56,340 --> 00:26:57,720
That we put a seal on it.

369
00:26:57,720 --> 00:27:00,060
Yeah, I remember.

370
00:27:00,060 --> 00:27:02,390
I really wanted to use that wish,

371
00:27:02,390 --> 00:27:06,320
but I patiently saved it up, you know, right?

372
00:27:06,320 --> 00:27:08,350
What's your wish?

373
00:27:10,490 --> 00:27:14,220
What you were about to say, don't say it.

374
00:27:16,710 --> 00:27:22,960
Of course, I know that while I love you, 
you can't love me back,

375
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:24,730
and I'm a little unhappy.

376
00:27:24,730 --> 00:27:29,540
But still, if you weren't beside me, 
I'd really be unhappy.

377
00:27:32,590 --> 00:27:35,530
So, don't say it.

378
00:27:36,850 --> 00:27:39,310
What you were about to say.

379
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:59,640
The care nurse said that Song Yi had come by.

380
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:01,030
Yeah.

381
00:28:01,770 --> 00:28:05,520
 Actually, he came by and kept asking.

382
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,560
 So I told him.

383
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:09,680
 That you were Yoo Ra unni's boyfriend.

384
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:14,270
 But did you tell that to anyone other than the detective?

385
00:28:14,270 --> 00:28:16,580
 Other than Hui Kyeong...

386
00:28:17,940 --> 00:28:19,320
Oh, yeah,

387
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:25,430
Song Yi said that she had said something 
to you regarding the deceased Han Yoo Ra.

388
00:28:25,430 --> 00:28:27,360
Yeah, she did.

389
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:29,170
What did she say?

390
00:28:29,820 --> 00:28:34,100
Their relationship wasn't good. 
And that it was tiring because of Han Yoo Ra.

391
00:28:34,100 --> 00:28:36,300
That she talked a lot of trash about Song Yi behind her back.

392
00:28:36,300 --> 00:28:39,360
And, what else?

393
00:28:39,360 --> 00:28:41,010
What else?

394
00:28:42,180 --> 00:28:43,140
What?

395
00:28:43,140 --> 00:28:48,270
Did she not mention anything specific about 
Han Yoo Ra's incident?

396
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:53,000
Did she say something?

397
00:28:54,190 --> 00:28:55,750
About what?

398
00:28:57,110 --> 00:29:01,310
Just that Han Yoo Ra's suicide wasn't because of her
 and that she felt wronged.

399
00:29:01,310 --> 00:29:05,020
She did say something about it, but other than that, well...

400
00:29:09,960 --> 00:29:12,930
I must have hit something wrong when I fell.

401
00:29:13,650 --> 00:29:17,460
My recent memory feels like it's shattered in places.

402
00:29:19,080 --> 00:29:22,390
When I try to remember, I get dizzy.

403
00:29:22,390 --> 00:29:25,830
Yeah, there's no need to exert yourself.

404
00:29:25,830 --> 00:29:26,910
Get some rest.

405
00:29:26,910 --> 00:29:28,280
Okay.

406
00:29:47,040 --> 00:29:49,950
The hyung next door seems like a decent person.

407
00:29:49,950 --> 00:29:50,770
What?

408
00:29:50,770 --> 00:29:54,060
There are no bad people among people who love stars.

409
00:29:54,060 --> 00:29:59,350
If it's the kind of person who installs astronomical telescopes
at home and observes the stars, it goes without saying.

410
00:30:02,590 --> 00:30:05,960
That person isn't looking at the stars,

411
00:30:06,780 --> 00:30:09,020
but rather, he came from there.

412
00:30:09,020 --> 00:30:10,280
What?

413
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:12,410
Don't worry about it.

414
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:16,600
Do you think there's such things as aliens?

415
00:30:16,600 --> 00:30:18,550
Of course there are, you don't think so?

416
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:22,380
To put it bluntly, I think an alien could be living next door.

417
00:30:22,380 --> 00:30:24,610
I'm the kind of person who believes that.

418
00:30:27,850 --> 00:30:30,160
You're a genius.

419
00:30:37,150 --> 00:30:40,340
Do Min Joon.

420
00:30:46,870 --> 00:30:49,690
What?

421
00:30:51,670 --> 00:30:52,940
Awesome!

422
00:30:52,940 --> 00:30:54,000
Why did you call?

423
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:56,620
To see whether you can actually hear or not.

424
00:30:56,620 --> 00:30:58,650
Are you kidding?

425
00:30:58,650 --> 00:31:01,020
Ah, Do Min Joon! Do Min Joon!

426
00:31:01,020 --> 00:31:03,070
Even still, you can just go back in like that?

427
00:31:03,070 --> 00:31:06,170
I didn't call you to see if you heard it or not.

428
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:09,630
But, because I want to see you.

429
00:31:09,630 --> 00:31:12,610
I called you because I wanted to see you.

430
00:31:12,610 --> 00:31:13,700
Okay?

431
00:31:13,700 --> 00:31:16,350
I said I called you because I missed you.

432
00:31:17,610 --> 00:31:21,390
He's rather petty and narrow-minded. Seriously.

433
00:31:21,390 --> 00:31:24,930
You scared me.

434
00:31:24,930 --> 00:31:27,620
How on earth....

435
00:31:27,620 --> 00:31:31,810
I can never get used to this no matter 
how many times I see it.

436
00:31:33,030 --> 00:31:35,940
Petty? Narrow-minded?

437
00:31:35,940 --> 00:31:38,000
No, I didn't mean...

438
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:41,170
Let go. Let me go!

439
00:31:41,170 --> 00:31:43,610
Let go.

440
00:31:43,610 --> 00:31:46,310
I told you to let go! Seriously!

441
00:31:46,310 --> 00:31:48,200
Let go! Let go!

442
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:58,820
You aren't going to give that to me?

443
00:31:58,820 --> 00:32:00,460
You don't need coffee since you're young!

444
00:32:00,460 --> 00:32:01,460
Then why are there two cups?

445
00:32:01,460 --> 00:32:04,160
I'm going to drink them all. 
I have to memorize my lines, but I'm sleepy.

446
00:32:04,160 --> 00:32:06,120
Why?

447
00:32:16,810 --> 00:32:18,370
By the way...

448
00:32:18,370 --> 00:32:24,090
Did your father also come from another star, just like you?

449
00:32:24,090 --> 00:32:26,640
Father?

450
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:28,610
Ah.

451
00:32:28,610 --> 00:32:30,860
Truthfully, he isn't my father.

452
00:32:30,860 --> 00:32:33,350
He is someone like my father.

453
00:32:33,350 --> 00:32:35,630
He's not your real father?

454
00:32:35,630 --> 00:32:36,690
No.

455
00:32:39,550 --> 00:32:42,750
Then you don't have any family?

456
00:32:42,750 --> 00:32:45,370
You know that's not possible.

457
00:32:45,370 --> 00:32:47,450
I see.

458
00:32:47,450 --> 00:32:51,400
You lived by yourself for such a long time
 without any family, then?

459
00:32:56,730 --> 00:32:59,320
I have happy news.

460
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:03,100
I met my father this time.

461
00:33:03,100 --> 00:33:06,050
Because of the accident, I was shocked and
 had a hard time. But,

462
00:33:06,050 --> 00:33:09,070
thanks to that, I met my father again.

463
00:33:09,070 --> 00:33:12,060
It isn't like I can live together with him right now, but...

464
00:33:12,060 --> 00:33:18,130
Being able to see him whenever I call
 gives me a strange sense of security.

465
00:33:18,130 --> 00:33:21,020
Something that was once heavy on my heart

466
00:33:21,020 --> 00:33:24,560
feels like it disappeared.

467
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:27,220
That is a relief.

468
00:33:33,590 --> 00:33:36,150
Do Min Joon,

469
00:33:36,150 --> 00:33:40,100
you have me now.

470
00:33:40,100 --> 00:33:43,470
I will stay by your side for a long long time,

471
00:33:43,470 --> 00:33:47,250
without running away.

472
00:33:53,650 --> 00:33:56,440
What?

473
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:57,530
Why are you like that?

474
00:33:57,530 --> 00:34:00,200
But Do Min Joon...

475
00:34:01,930 --> 00:34:04,280
Will your face stay like this?

476
00:34:04,280 --> 00:34:05,350
Huh?

477
00:34:05,350 --> 00:34:07,430
I guess so.

478
00:34:07,430 --> 00:34:11,980
Even when I saw the picture from 100 years ago, only your 
hairstyle was different and your face was exactly as it is.

479
00:34:11,980 --> 00:34:14,730
What will happen (to your face)?

480
00:34:17,550 --> 00:34:20,310
Time on our star

481
00:34:20,310 --> 00:34:24,070
and time here are very different.

482
00:34:24,070 --> 00:34:25,880
The rate of aging as well.

483
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:28,200
Then what will I do?

484
00:34:28,200 --> 00:34:30,480
My skin will sag and I'll get wrinkles,

485
00:34:30,480 --> 00:34:35,270
I'll get more gray hair and my back will become more bent.
 I'll become a little old grandmother!

486
00:34:35,270 --> 00:34:37,140
Calm down. You will be pretty even if you get old.

487
00:34:37,140 --> 00:34:41,870
Forget it! This is why women in vampire movies
 have their necks bitten in order to become vampires too.

488
00:34:41,870 --> 00:34:47,090
Men don't age and look cool. But women keep aging, 
so even if they're together, it isn't a happy ending!

489
00:34:47,090 --> 00:34:48,190
Cheon Song Yi!

490
00:34:48,190 --> 00:34:51,360
I don't want to hear anything now. I will go in first.

491
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:54,460
The cold air can age my skin faster.

492
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:12,330
Will this be enough?

493
00:35:14,170 --> 00:35:17,280
I am ruined.

494
00:35:20,620 --> 00:35:22,710
I can't (get old).

495
00:35:22,710 --> 00:35:24,860
I can't!

496
00:35:24,860 --> 00:35:26,550
I'm almost thirty.

497
00:35:27,750 --> 00:35:30,300
What should I do?

498
00:35:31,260 --> 00:35:36,420
 Today, for the aging prevention special, we have 45-year old
 "young face beauty," Ms. Park Min Hee on our show.

499
00:35:36,420 --> 00:35:40,240
 You brought a rubber glove.
 What do you do with this?

500
00:35:43,350 --> 00:35:48,620
 When you blow air into a rubber glove like this, 
your lung capacity increases and free radical oxygen is removed,

501
00:35:48,620 --> 00:35:51,090
 which helps prevent aging skin.

502
00:35:51,090 --> 00:35:53,920
 Wow, so that's why...

503
00:36:02,920 --> 00:36:07,120
I suppose Cheon Song Yi could think 
like that from her perspective.

504
00:36:07,120 --> 00:36:11,760
But that's not what's important, is it?

505
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:15,360
After a month, you will soon....

506
00:36:29,870 --> 00:36:34,270
  I think there is a tap on your bag.

507
00:36:34,270 --> 00:36:37,640
  Please talk naturally.

508
00:36:39,690 --> 00:36:41,520
By the way,

509
00:36:41,520 --> 00:36:44,540
I met Managing Director Lee Jae Kyeong.

510
00:36:44,540 --> 00:36:47,800
Ah, is that so?

511
00:36:47,800 --> 00:36:51,790
 He asked me to help him. That he'd watch my back.

512
00:36:51,790 --> 00:36:55,300
So what did you say to him?

513
00:36:55,300 --> 00:36:57,730
I told him I would think about it.

514
00:36:57,730 --> 00:36:59,920
I didn't think it was a bad offer.

515
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:03,140
Because I just need to protect Cheon Song Yi in any case.

516
00:37:03,140 --> 00:37:05,190
Even then...

517
00:37:07,020 --> 00:37:08,690
I...

518
00:37:08,690 --> 00:37:14,140
put out a condition that he would stay quiet and 
not harm anyone for the time being.

519
00:37:15,540 --> 00:37:21,060
I plan to be of assistance if that promise is kept.

520
00:37:21,060 --> 00:37:22,770
  Really?

521
00:37:25,810 --> 00:37:27,620
